%global packname  SETPath
%global packver   1.0
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          1.0
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          Spiked Eigenvalue Test for Pathway data

License:          GPL-2
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
Tests gene expression data from a biological pathway for biologically
meaningful differences in the eigenstructure between two classes.
Specifically, it tests the null hypothesis that the two classes' leading
eigenvalues and sums of eigenvalues are equal.  A pathway's leading
eigenvalue arguably represents the total variability due to variability in
pathway activity, while the sum of all its eigenvalues represents the
variability due to pathway activity and to other, unregulated causes.
Implementation of the method described in Danaher (2015),
"Covariance-based analyses of biological pathways".

